282
00:20:05,590 --> 00:20:07,630
She didn't submit any evidence.

283
00:20:10,470 --> 00:20:12,220
There's no actual evidence then?

284
00:20:16,890 --> 00:20:19,400
Did you assault her?

285
00:20:22,980 --> 00:20:25,530
Does it matter? There's no evidence.

286
00:20:25,610 --> 00:20:28,200
If it's true, now is the time to speak up.

287
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:31,700
That way, I can respond properly.

288
00:20:33,370 --> 00:20:34,370
It's not true.

289
00:20:36,370 --> 00:20:39,920
Even according to her,
it was just one time, not multiple.

290
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,330
So not even once?

291
00:20:46,210 --> 00:20:47,380
No.

292
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:50,050
Not by my standards.

293
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,890
- What about verbal abuse?
- I didn't do that either.

294
00:20:56,980 --> 00:20:59,020
Not by my standards.

295
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,200
All right.

296
00:21:09,910 --> 00:21:14,160
I'll submit a written statement
firmly denying everything on that premise.

297
00:21:15,950 --> 00:21:18,250
What? You don't believe me?

298
00:21:18,330 --> 00:21:21,120
Whether I believe you or not
isn't that important.

299
00:21:21,210 --> 00:21:23,170
How is that not important?

300
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:28,510
How can I let someone represent me
if they don't believe me?

301
00:21:33,090 --> 00:21:37,850
My job is to help you properly exercise
your right to defend yourself.

302
00:21:38,930 --> 00:21:42,520
What I believe
doesn't change how I do my job.

303
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:44,150
So don't worry about that.

304
00:22:10,630 --> 00:22:13,720
Since the plaintiff's wife
died instantly in the accident,

305
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:17,760
there's no basis for a claim
against the defendant's husband.

306
00:22:17,850 --> 00:22:20,770
A deceased person
can't be granted any legal rights.

307
00:22:22,140 --> 00:22:23,900
The Supreme Court has repeatedly ruled

308
00:22:23,980 --> 00:22:27,400
that even in cases of instant death,
the right to claim damages

309
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:30,490
is still recognized in that brief moment.

310
00:22:30,570 --> 00:22:32,530
Kim Minkyung knew
Mr. Song was drunk driving

311
00:22:32,610 --> 00:22:34,450
but turned a blind eye to it,

312
00:22:34,530 --> 00:22:36,200
so that fault reduces the payout.

313
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:38,990
That said,
the plaintiff's claim for damages

314
00:22:39,080 --> 00:22:41,910
has nothing to do with drunk driving.

315
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:46,420
The claim also includes
compensation for the affair,

316
00:22:46,500 --> 00:22:49,050
so that needs to be assessed separately.

317
00:22:49,130 --> 00:22:53,340
Okay, all of that
is already in the written submission,

318
00:22:53,430 --> 00:22:54,550
so let's leave it there.

319
00:22:55,430 --> 00:22:58,680
The defendants haven't renounced
their inheritance, correct?

320
00:22:59,260 --> 00:23:03,770
