523
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:46,100
Fill me in on yesterday's
Champions League game then.

524
00:41:46,180 --> 00:41:48,890
- Who won?
- The Champions League?

525
00:41:49,850 --> 00:41:51,060
I don't watch soccer.

526
00:41:51,150 --> 00:41:52,690
Unbelievable.

527
00:41:53,560 --> 00:41:55,320
What kind of idiot did they send?

528
00:41:55,400 --> 00:41:57,150
Then, how about this?

529
00:41:57,900 --> 00:42:01,360
You were arrested for stock manipulation.
Let's talk about the case.

530
00:42:01,450 --> 00:42:02,820
I'll talk about the case

531
00:42:03,530 --> 00:42:05,780
with my lawyer
who's actually representing me.

532
00:42:06,370 --> 00:42:08,120
You're not here to represent me.

533
00:42:09,250 --> 00:42:11,210
You think you're here as a lawyer?

534
00:42:11,790 --> 00:42:13,500
You're a loser keeping me company.

535
00:42:17,340 --> 00:42:18,510
When does this end?

536
00:42:36,940 --> 00:42:39,650
- Where are you coming back from?
- I had a trial. You too?

537
00:42:40,440 --> 00:42:41,490
No, I…

538
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:44,240
had a prison visit.

539
00:42:44,820 --> 00:42:45,820
I see.

540
00:42:55,750 --> 00:42:56,750
What is it?

541
00:42:57,170 --> 00:42:58,170
What?

542
00:42:58,250 --> 00:43:01,340
It's just I've never seen you
with such a serious expression before.

543
00:43:02,010 --> 00:43:03,010
Really?

544
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:07,350
Or are you not upset
and just out of energy?

545
00:43:08,180 --> 00:43:09,430
What, is something wrong?

546
00:43:10,560 --> 00:43:11,560
No.

547
00:43:12,140 --> 00:43:14,350
I'm just bored
because nothing's going on at all.

548
00:43:15,150 --> 00:43:17,940
Man, I wish I could take on
an exciting case for once.

549
00:43:18,020 --> 00:43:19,650
Something that feels
worth doing.

550
00:43:20,690 --> 00:43:22,990
What kind of case
was that prison visit for?

551
00:43:23,700 --> 00:43:25,070
Oh, that.

552
00:43:25,570 --> 00:43:26,780
Some stock manipulation.

553
00:43:27,780 --> 00:43:29,620
There must be a lot of victims then.

554
00:43:30,200 --> 00:43:33,160
The problem is,
no one knows if there's a lot or not.

555
00:43:34,620 --> 00:43:36,130
You didn't get the records yet?

556
00:43:37,040 --> 00:43:40,590
Yeah, I got them. Of course, I did.

557
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:43,510
But why do I feel so gloomy?

558
00:43:44,220 --> 00:43:46,340
Everyone's been so down.
Maybe I caught it too.

559
00:43:48,010 --> 00:43:50,890
Yeah, everyone's been looking down lately.

560
00:43:53,430 --> 00:43:54,560
- Just in case…
- Yes?

561
00:43:54,640 --> 00:43:58,270
If they ask something
that's difficult to answer, I'll help out.

562
00:43:58,360 --> 00:43:59,690
So don't worry too much.

563
00:43:59,770 --> 00:44:00,860
Okay, thank you.

564
00:44:02,650 --> 00:44:03,780
All rise.

565
00:44:19,500 --> 00:44:20,590
Please be seated.

566
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:28,840
I know this must be a difficult case
for you to attend in person today,

567
00:44:29,340 --> 00:44:32,930
so I'd like to thank both parties
for making the time to be here.

568
00:44:33,470 --> 00:44:34,890
Given the nature of this case,

569
00:44:34,980 --> 00:44:39,150
both sides were, in a way,
victims of the affair.

570
00:44:39,650 --> 00:44:43,730
So we felt it was best to help you
reach an agreement peacefully

571
00:44:43,820 --> 00:44:46,400
without causing further harm.

572
00:44:46,490 --> 00:44:48,360
That's why we called you here today.

573
00:44:49,620 --> 00:44:52,870
We know this is painful,

574
00:44:53,540 --> 00:44:57,290
and we hope you understand
the court deeply regrets

575
00:44:57,370 --> 00:44:59,330
having you to appear in person as well.

576
00:45:02,170 --> 00:45:04,420
Let's try to wrap this up
through mediation today.

577
00:45:04,500 --> 00:45:06,260
Yes, I'll do that.

578
00:45:11,430 --> 00:45:13,640
Did you really regret it?

579
00:45:16,560 --> 00:45:19,650
Do you really understand how painful

580
00:45:20,520 --> 00:45:21,520
this is for us?

581
00:45:25,650 --> 00:45:28,150
We sincerely hope this can be resolved,

582
00:45:28,650 --> 00:45:32,700
so both of you can move on
and start anew--

583
00:45:32,780 --> 00:45:34,120
Move on?

584
00:45:36,250 --> 00:45:39,210
Peacefully without causing further harm?

585
00:45:41,710 --> 00:45:43,130
You think that's possible?

586
00:45:43,210 --> 00:45:45,550
Do you think settling with him

587
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:48,010
will fix everything?

588
00:45:51,010 --> 00:45:52,050
Geez.

589
00:45:53,550 --> 00:45:54,600
If I had just

590
00:45:55,760 --> 00:45:57,720
given up my inheritance,

591
00:45:58,770 --> 00:46:01,850
I wouldn't have had to go through
the ordeal of paying damages

592
00:46:02,350 --> 00:46:04,110
to my husband's mistress.

593
00:46:07,190 --> 00:46:09,530
But I have two kids to feed.

594
00:46:11,280 --> 00:46:15,740
And we need that house
under Song Yeongcheol's name to survive.

595
00:46:18,160 --> 00:46:19,160
I was…

596
00:46:19,790 --> 00:46:22,330
so pathetic
that I couldn't give up my inheritance.

597
00:46:24,080 --> 00:46:27,590
You have no idea how it feels
to suffer this humiliation.

598
00:46:32,470 --> 00:46:35,430
That's why instead of leaving it
to the court,

599
00:46:35,510 --> 00:46:38,350
we brought both parties here
to settle it themselves.

600
00:46:38,430 --> 00:46:39,850
So please try to stay calm.

601
00:46:39,930 --> 00:46:41,390
Are you saying

602
00:46:41,890 --> 00:46:44,900
if I handle things myself and settle,
I'll get a fresh start?

603
00:46:46,060 --> 00:46:49,440
Do you think he feels at peace right now?

604
00:46:58,330 --> 00:46:59,660
I mean,

605
00:47:01,620 --> 00:47:03,580
if this were something I did,

606
00:47:05,580 --> 00:47:08,460
I'd take full responsibility.

607
00:47:09,250 --> 00:47:14,010
But I didn't do any of this!

608
00:47:23,230 --> 00:47:24,640
There's no way

609
00:47:25,980 --> 00:47:27,270
that I can personally

610
00:47:28,230 --> 00:47:31,570
hand over the money
to my husband's mistress.

611
00:47:31,650 --> 00:47:33,610
So please, just give a verdict.

612
00:47:33,700 --> 00:47:36,030
Just take it from me by force.

613
00:47:36,110 --> 00:47:40,200
I absolutely cannot bring myself
to personally pay them.

614
00:48:00,220 --> 00:48:01,680
This is driving me crazy.

615
00:48:02,810 --> 00:48:06,980
DEFENDANT PARK SUJEONG

616
00:48:16,490 --> 00:48:18,910
This will confirm
that the divorce finalized

617
00:48:18,990 --> 00:48:20,990
and there are no remaining claims

618
00:48:21,080 --> 00:48:24,330
for anything owed,
such as alimony or asset division.

619
00:48:24,870 --> 00:48:30,460
COUNSEL AHN JUHYEONG

620
00:48:55,650 --> 00:48:57,530
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm fine.

621
00:48:58,030 --> 00:49:00,950
So in this case,
there likely will be one more trial date.

622
00:49:01,030 --> 00:49:03,830
If things wrap up then,
they'll set the date for the verdict.

623
00:49:04,660 --> 00:49:06,160
Yes, I understand.

624
00:49:09,330 --> 00:49:12,210
Excuse me. Thank you for your time.

625
00:49:17,130 --> 00:49:18,800
Does someone like you

626
00:49:19,680 --> 00:49:22,050
even understand how someone like me feels?

627
00:49:23,930 --> 00:49:25,020
Let's go now.

628
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:28,480
People like you
are born into nice families

629
00:49:28,560 --> 00:49:30,730
and go to expensive law schools,

630
00:49:30,810 --> 00:49:33,520
where it's easier
to become a lawyer.

631
00:49:34,150 --> 00:49:36,400
How could you even relate
to something like this?

632
00:49:37,320 --> 00:49:38,950
You named my kids as defendants!

633
00:49:40,820 --> 00:49:44,120
You shouldn't live your life like that.

634
00:49:44,950 --> 00:49:45,990
Let's go.

635
00:49:48,290 --> 00:49:51,000
I looked you up to see
what kind of person you were.

636
00:49:51,080 --> 00:49:53,210
You're not the only one
who looked into things!

637
00:49:59,220 --> 00:50:01,220
- Attorney Ha.
- Yes?

638
00:50:01,300 --> 00:50:04,050
- Let's just go.
- Yes, let's go.

639
00:50:28,370 --> 00:50:31,410
The case ended in your favor,
so you won't need to come in anymore.

640
00:50:32,920 --> 00:50:37,210
How could I not show up
after hearing such good news?

641
00:50:44,340 --> 00:50:46,390
It's nothing much.
Just a gift certificate.

642
00:50:46,470 --> 00:50:48,270
I wanted to show my thanks.

643
00:50:49,390 --> 00:50:51,690
- So please take it.
- No, it's okay.

644
00:50:52,980 --> 00:50:53,980
Come on.

645
00:50:54,900 --> 00:50:56,650
Take it!

646
00:50:58,020 --> 00:51:01,320
You pulled off a clean win.

647
00:51:05,240 --> 00:51:07,280
Yes, thank you.

648
00:51:13,460 --> 00:51:17,380
I'm so glad I had you take the case.

649
00:51:20,590 --> 00:51:21,840
I made

650
00:51:22,670 --> 00:51:25,760
a specific request
when I talked to Mr. Na.

651
00:51:26,720 --> 00:51:30,810
I asked for you
to be put on my case.

652
00:51:32,140 --> 00:51:33,560
- Me?
- Yes.

653
00:51:33,640 --> 00:51:35,690
You, Attorney Ahn Juhyeong.

654
00:51:46,950 --> 00:51:51,750
I figured if she had to deal with her ex,
it would make her uncomfortable.

655
00:51:52,790 --> 00:51:54,120
It looks like I was right.

656
00:51:59,340 --> 00:52:00,750
You look very surprised.

657
00:52:01,550 --> 00:52:02,590
I see.

658
00:52:04,840 --> 00:52:07,300
- You came to me on purpose?
- Yes.

659
00:52:07,390 --> 00:52:09,890
I came here on purpose to buy you.

660
00:52:12,140 --> 00:52:14,270
We're getting divorced anyway.

661
00:52:14,350 --> 00:52:17,350
What's the point of being polite?
It does no good for me.

662
00:52:17,440 --> 00:52:18,860
How did you find out about me?

663
00:52:20,150 --> 00:52:21,150
What?

664
00:52:22,030 --> 00:52:23,570
Afraid Sujeong talked about you?

665
00:52:23,650 --> 00:52:25,280
How did you find out?

666
00:52:30,200 --> 00:52:31,330
Remember Jung Jihun?

667
00:52:32,290 --> 00:52:33,450
Sujeong's friend?

668
00:52:34,040 --> 00:52:36,120
He's always been a nuisance.

669
00:52:36,960 --> 00:52:39,420
He's foolish and doesn't have
a filter when he talks.

670
00:52:41,540 --> 00:52:44,840
He once got drunk in front of me
and started talking about you.

671
00:52:46,840 --> 00:52:47,880
You don't know him?

672
00:52:48,470 --> 00:52:49,640
Not really.

673
00:52:49,720 --> 00:52:51,100
It doesn't ring a bell.

674
00:52:55,680 --> 00:52:56,690
Really?

675
00:52:57,520 --> 00:52:58,520
Then,

676
00:52:59,560 --> 00:53:02,190
that's all the more reason to take this.

677
00:53:02,820 --> 00:53:03,860
Here.

678
00:53:05,150 --> 00:53:06,150
Good work.

679
00:53:07,200 --> 00:53:08,200
Enjoy it.

680
00:53:09,070 --> 00:53:11,030
Buy yourself something nice.

681
00:53:12,280 --> 00:53:14,080
DIVORCE
CHA JEONGHO, PARK SUJEONG

682
00:53:14,160 --> 00:53:17,120
SETTLEMENT REACHED

683
00:53:18,420 --> 00:53:19,960
It looks like they settled.

684
00:53:20,500 --> 00:53:21,630
DEFENDANT PARK SUJEONG

685
00:53:21,710 --> 00:53:25,880
LAW GROUP HYUNGMIN
ATTORNEY IN CHARGE: AHN JUHYEONG

686
00:53:44,770 --> 00:53:46,230
AHN JUHYEONG

687
00:53:46,320 --> 00:53:48,950
THANKS FOR TODAY
I'LL TREAT YOU NEXT TIME

688
00:53:49,030 --> 00:53:51,360
OKAY, GOOD NIGHT

689
00:53:57,000 --> 00:54:00,830
ARE YOU OKAY?

690
00:54:30,900 --> 00:54:32,320
I didn't think it would rip.

691
00:54:32,990 --> 00:54:34,450
I guess you didn't put in much.

692
00:54:36,490 --> 00:54:37,580
Thank you for the gift.

693
00:54:45,130 --> 00:54:47,960
I can't believe there's someone
who would turn down cash.

694
00:54:49,210 --> 00:54:52,050
It was probably worth
as much as your monthly salary.

695
00:54:52,630 --> 00:54:55,550
Says the guy who sought me out
just to save 10 million won.

696
00:54:56,600 --> 00:55:00,480
Geez, how am I supposed buy a lawyer
if you make me feel so self-conscious?

697
00:55:01,890 --> 00:55:02,940
I paid

698
00:55:03,850 --> 00:55:06,310
with my money to buy you.

699
00:55:06,980 --> 00:55:08,020
Don't forget that.

700
00:55:08,110 --> 00:55:11,150
If it weren't for that,
I wouldn't bother with trash like you.

701
00:55:12,360 --> 00:55:15,410
Since that's over, just quietly get lost.

702
00:55:15,490 --> 00:55:16,740
You little…

703
00:55:16,820 --> 00:55:18,580
Hey.

704
00:55:19,330 --> 00:55:20,580
Hey, you…

705
00:55:23,750 --> 00:55:25,670
We would have evidence here this time.

706
00:55:27,750 --> 00:55:29,420
And I don't let things slide.

707
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:11,380
DIVORCE

708
00:56:11,460 --> 00:56:13,720
PLAINTIFF CHA JEONGHO
DEFENDANT PARK SUJEONG

709
00:56:22,600 --> 00:56:23,810
I'm sorry.

710
00:57:24,870 --> 00:57:25,910
Excuse me.

711
00:57:28,670 --> 00:57:31,540
Juhyeong already left. You should go.

712
00:57:55,610 --> 00:57:57,150
I crossed the line.

713
00:57:59,400 --> 00:58:00,820
Why did I do that?

714
00:58:50,460 --> 00:58:51,580
INMATE NAME: JANG SUGIL

715
00:58:51,660 --> 00:58:54,170
<i>You think you're here as a lawyer?</i>

716
00:58:54,250 --> 00:58:55,920
<i>You're a loser keeping me company.</i>

717
00:59:04,720 --> 00:59:06,720
<i>People like you</i>
<i>are born into nice families</i>

718
00:59:06,800 --> 00:59:09,100
<i>and go to expensive law schools,</i>

719
00:59:09,180 --> 00:59:11,640
<i>where it's easier</i>
<i>to become a lawyer.</i>

720
00:59:12,350 --> 00:59:14,600
<i>How could you even relate</i>
<i>to something like this?</i>

721
00:59:27,910 --> 00:59:29,120
<i>Are you okay?</i>

722
00:59:41,630 --> 00:59:45,300
<i>Now, you're not Cha Jeongho's attorney</i>
<i>and just Ahn Juhyeong, right?</i>

723
01:00:07,660 --> 01:00:14,620
Law and The City

724
01:00:44,490 --> 01:00:48,200
Law and The City

725
01:00:48,280 --> 01:00:50,410
<i>I crossed the line. I'm sorry.</i>

726
01:00:50,490 --> 01:00:52,620
What do you need
that fancy law license for?

727
01:00:54,290 --> 01:00:55,620
Who are you, Mister?

728
01:00:55,710 --> 01:00:57,750
<i>We're too young</i>
<i>to be criminally responsible.</i>

729
01:00:57,830 --> 01:01:00,040
That would make me
too scared to have kids.

730
01:01:00,500 --> 01:01:03,460
He always brings girls here
to woo them.

731
01:01:03,550 --> 01:01:04,800
<i>What do you do to woo them?</i>

732
01:01:05,380 --> 01:01:06,670
<i>But it won't work for Huiji.</i>

733
01:01:06,760 --> 01:01:08,720
<i>Juhyeong, I'm a busy person too.</i>

734
01:01:08,800 --> 01:01:11,430
- Attorney Ha Sanggi?
<i>- I bet someone got him that job.</i>

735
01:01:11,510 --> 01:01:12,890
<i>Having fun playing a commoner?</i>

736
01:01:13,850 --> 01:01:14,970
<i>Actually…</i>

737
01:01:16,100 --> 01:01:17,770
<i>Why don't you have a meal with me?</i>

738
01:01:18,730 --> 01:01:19,810
<i>A promise is a promise.</i>

739
01:01:28,990 --> 01:01:30,990
Translated by Hye Min Eom